                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the donor (fol. 91vb);
                           incipits of Text I and its subsections (a few lines are rubricated,
                           alternating with black lines, on fols. 1ra-rb, 10va-vb); incipit of Text
                           II; the word säläm in Text I-1 and from Text I-4 up to Text I-14; the
                           word ʾO-za-...and the following verbal form in Text I-2; the word
                           tämaḫǝḍänku in Text I-3; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of
                           Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The hand is characterized
                        by:</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> - the letter ለ has nearly vertical
                        right leg;
                        </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic"> - the letter ሥ presents a smaller
                        right loop; the letter ሣ has a smaller left
                        loop.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#85vb">f. 85vb</locus>
                           <desc>l.1: Ownership note. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"> <locus target="#85vb">85vb</locus>: ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘቄስ፡
                              ተስፋ፡ ሥላሴ፡ ሣምራ፡ ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘፈሐቃ፡ ውጉዝ፡ ይኩን።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#85vb">85vb</locus>: This book is of priest Tasfā
                              Śǝllāse (of) Śamra. The one who stole it or the one who scratched
                              (what is written in it), shall be excommunicated. </quote>
                           <note> </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2"> <locus target="#93rb">f. 93rb</locus>
                           <desc>l.7: ʾAsmat-prayer.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#93rb">93rb</locus> l.7: በስመ፡ አብ፡ በል፡ ከል፡ ተከልከል ፯ጊዜ፡
                              ሔጄርጄ፡ ፯ጊዜ፡ ጉሐጄን፡ ወጉበርጄን፯ጊዜ፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">  </quote>
                           <note> </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title of Text I is crudely written on the front
                           leather cover with yellow paint.
 - Titles of the works (<locus target="#8r">8r</locus> መልክአ፡ ማርያም፡ Malkǝʾa Māryām, <locus target="#9r">9r</locus> (መልክአ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ Malkǝʾa ʾIyasus) are crudely
                           written in blue pen in the upper margins.
 - Short ownership note
                           (ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘማይ፡ አንበሳ፡) is crudely written in a recent hand, below Additio 1:
                              <locus target="#85vb">85vb</locus>.
 - Note, correction (?)
                           written in the upper margin of <locus target="#90vb">90vb</locus>.
 -
                           Several corrections written interlineally: e.g., <locus target="#6ra">6ra</locus>, 32vb, 60rb, 67rb, 90vb, 91ra. 
 - Writing excercise:
                              <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>, 7v, 8r, 25r, 93v.
 - Pen trials:
                              <locus target="#48r">48r</locus>, 48v, 50r, 50v, 51v, 55r, 61v,
                           93v.- Shelfmark C4-IV-78 (<locus target="#41r">41r</locus>)</item>
                     </list>
